Officer of The First Seal - <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://firstseal.tripod.com/">firstseal.tripod.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujaikarhalfelf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaikar HalfElf</A></span><br> <b>Everybody's Favorite Hero</b><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/23/00 1:29:35 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.feir-dal.net/jaikarphoto.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: timing taunts???</span><hr size=1> At times, ye may wish ta hold back on yer Tauntin' until the foe turns its attention ta sumone else (likes a sissy caster). After all, if the creature's already whackin' on ye, there ain't no real reason ta call it more names -- just kill it. This way, ye ain't sittin' there screamin' at the Taunt hotkey ta refresh while ye watches yer cleric git eaten. <p><a href="http://www.feir-dal.net/tavern/bios/Jaikar.html"><IMG SRC="http://www.feir-dal.net/JaikarSig.JPG"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vanzant>VanZant</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/23/00 5:00:32 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/crimsondragons2000/vanzy.jpg border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: timing taunts???</span><hr size=1> Taunts...<br>
<br>
Do what Jaikar says for one thing... that way when the mob does turn to another member of your party you can use taunt instantly and dont have to wait for it to refresh.<br>
<br>
Also, this is just a theory of mine.. but it's the way I've always done things.  Try using a pattern of disarm, kick then taunt.  It seems to me like your taunts have a better chance of working when you piss em off a little with a disarm and a kick first, but I couldn't give ya any real data to support that theory.<br>
<br>
