<a href=mailto:vanhammer@hotmail.com><font color=navy><i><b>Vanhammer@hotmail.com</b></i></font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> kether</span><br> <b>is too scared to Register</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(10/23/00 10:56:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   taunt</span><hr size=1> Yes, don't waste taunt when it is already hittig you.<br>
Just kill it.<br>
<br>
When it ISN'T attacking you, use every taunting method:<br>
1. Taunt  (if successful check is made, you are new target)<br>
2. Disarm  (increases hatred of you)<br>
3. Kick  (damage increases you hate rank)<br>
<br>
If 1 works you are done.  Do that first.<br>
Two and three MAY work, but only if you were close to the top anyway.  They ADD hatred.  Taunt makes you MOST hated (at the time) when it works.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kether<br>
Paladin - E'ci<br>
