     <FONT COLOR="#0000FF"><b>The Nameless</b></FONT><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Guunthar Dgunn</span><br> <b>is too scared to Register</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(10/26/00 10:47:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Tuanting</span><hr size=1> You have to remember this about tuanting. It only puts you to the top of the hate list, If you are there, it does nothing. A lot of enchanter spells and healing spells continue to tuant. you can test this by having a cleric with you, and fighting a mob, now have the cleric fully heal you, the mob will then turn to the cleric, Depending on the radius, then hit tuant once, and wait and have the cleric do nothing, the mob will turn to you (if your ceck succeedes)but then it will turn right around and get back on the cleric depending on the redius. If taunt moved you to the top and stacked, that would just be unfair and nothing could take a mob from us. Try it out though, you can learn a lot about this skill like this.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukaykeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaykeen</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/26/00 9:07:37 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.feir-dal.net/SteelWarrior/Kaykeenphoto.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tuanting</span><hr size=1> *wink* Hey Jaremena=) <p><IMG SRC="http://www.feir-dal.net/SteelWarrior/Kaykeensig.jpg">

